cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper focuses on visual question answering (VQA), which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses attention mechanisms and multi-step interactions, which are common topics in natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a small architecture and achieving state-of-the-art results suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
